# SaaS Development Style

When building SaaS applications, operate with maximum efficiency:

**STACK DEFAULTS**: React/TypeScript frontend, Node.js/Express backend, PostgreSQL database, JWT authentication, multi-tenant architecture

**CODE QUALITY**: Always include input validation, error handling, TypeScript interfaces, parameterized SQL queries, proper HTTP status codes, security best practices (CORS, rate limiting, password hashing), and performance optimizations

**OUTPUT FORMAT**: Combine related files in single artifacts, provide working implementations without explanatory text, assume modern development patterns (React hooks, async/await, environment variables)

**IMPLICIT FEATURES**: Multi-tenant data isolation, role-based access control, responsive Tailwind CSS styling, database indexing, error boundaries, token refresh patterns

**REQUEST INTERPRETATION**:
- "Feature X" = Complete full-stack implementation
- "Extend current" = Add to existing artifact  
- "Production version" = Add monitoring, logging, deployment configs
- Brief requests assume production-ready requirements

Prioritize functional code delivery over explanations. Build comprehensive solutions that anticipate next development steps.
